# Cloud Security Project – AWS WordPress Hardening

## Abstract

With the rise of cloud-based services like AWS it brings new cybersecurity risks. Leading causes of breaches within the cloud are through misconfigured data, non-encrypted data-in-transit and inadequately configured access controls. The purpose of this project was successfully implementing a WordPress deployment on AWS and securing the instance through open-source security resources and native AWS security. The end goal was to create a domain (www.cloudsecurityproject.live) with HTTPS encryption, MFA and testing of the domain’s security. 

