# 3. Network Architecture

## VPC and Network Topology

A VPC was used instead of one EC2 instance because a VPC offers more control in terms of network segregation, routing and security.

Within the VPC, public and private subnets can be created as needed. Only the web server was intended to be accessible publicly as none of the backend servers were intended for public access.

Additionally, with custom route tables and security groups, control for network traffic could be established which decreases the risk of external exposure. 

