## Bastion Host

A bastion host was implemented for secure administrative access to the cloud environment.

The bastion host is located on Public Subnet B (10.0.16.0/20, us-east-1b) of the custom VPC with an associated elastic IP address (18.214.134.12) and only inbound SSH (22) access from my own trusted IP address.

The WordPress EC2 instance located in Public Subnet A maintains SSH access permissions from the bastion security group, and additional inbound HTTPS (443) and HTTP (80) access permissions from public Internet.

Public access to the administrative capabilities of the web server is restricted, meaning that exposure to attacks is reduced.

Access is secured via key authentication with the deployed project key pair.

Access is granted through the bastion host with an effective SSH connection:


This allows secure maintenance without public access to the application features.

---

## Subnets

The VPC consists of four subnets across two availability zones (us-east-1a and us-east-1b) for network segregation.

Public Subnet A has the first EC2 Instance, the hardened WordPress web server and Public Subnet B has the Bastion EC2 Instance.

These two subnets are public to have Internet access through an Internet Gateway but HTTPS and SSH access are restricted with AWS Security Groups.

Private Subnets A and B are reserved for services that may be exposed to the Internet at a later stage such as database or other backend services that do not need to be publicly available.

This subnet structure enhances security while enforcing the principle of least privilege and aligns with AWS best practices for cloud security architecture. 

---

## Security Groups

Two additional Security Groups were set up to create more secure network access for the Cloud Security Project VPC.

### Cloud Security Final Security Group

Implemented on the WordPress EC2 instance.

Allows:

- HTTPS (443)
- HTTP (80)

From anywhere (0.0.0.0/0)

Allows:

- SSH (22)

Only from the Bastion Final security group.

### Bastion Final Security Group

Allows:

- SSH (22)

Only from one trusted IP address.

This ensures the Bastion host must be accessed first before connecting to the WordPress EC2 instance.

---

## VPC Endpoint

A VPC Gateway Endpoint was created which means the AWS network can connect to Amazon S3 without public internet access.

The endpoint connects the VPC to S3 in the us-east-1 region.

Anything within Private Subnet A or Private Subnet B can communicate with S3 over AWS’s internal network.

