# 6. Technical Testing Approach

Security testing was performed using:

- Nmap
- Nikto

Baseline scans were taken before hardening and compared with scans after hardening.

---

## Nmap Baseline Scan

Results showed expected ports:

80 HTTP  
443 HTTPS


Port 22 was not exposed publicly due to Bastion configuration.

---

## HTTP Enumeration

Detected:

- Apache version disclosure
- Missing security headers
- TRACE method enabled
- Directory listing

---

## Hardening Measures

Changes applied to:
/etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf


Hardening included:

- Disable TRACE
- Remove server version
- Disable directory indexing
- Add security headers

---

## Nikto Baseline Scan

Identified:

- Missing headers
- Directory listing
- TRACE method enabled
- WordPress API exposure

---

## Nikto Post Hardening Scan

Second scan showed:

- reduced vulnerabilities
- WAF activity detected

Wordfence blocked over 100 malicious requests.

---

# 7. Findings & Risk Ratings

Risk levels were categorized as:

- Low
- Medium
- High

Based on CIA triad impact:

- Confidentiality
- Integrity
- Availability

Main vulnerabilities identified:

- Apache version disclosure
- Missing security headers
- TRACE method enabled
- Directory listing enabled
- WordPress information disclosure

All were mitigated through configuration hardening.

